
<Lesson stage="3" page="2" type="Reading Check">
<APageParagraph activityIntroClip="uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3"  pencil="p3" skipIntro="true">
   <paragraph>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>On July 2, 1900, a man introduced a new engineering wonder to the world.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>The machines to which he gave his name were expensive to build. </text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>As it turned out, they were also delicate.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
       </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>His name was Count Zeppelin.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>No one in the USA had heard of him at that time.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>However, the Zeppelin was to become a household word.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>      
   </paragraph>
   <paragraph>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>The Zeppelin was a giant rigid airship, which was filled with hydrogen gas.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Zeppelins were driven by two engines which were fixed below it.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>But the engines of the first Zeppelin were far too small to be effective.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>It had to be taken apart.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>Zeppelin 2 wasn't much better and was destroyed in a storm.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>But the Zeppelin 3 design worked well.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>The last Zeppelin, called the Hindenburg, was number 129.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
   </paragraph>
      <paragraph>
       <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>   
      <sentence>
         <text>By the 1920s, Britain, France, Italy and the USA were all building airships, but the Hindenburg impressed the whole world.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>The Hindenburg was 800 feet long and 135 feet wide.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>This is four times longer than a 747 airplane.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
  </paragraph>
  <paragraph>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>CR</text>
		  <clip></clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
         <text>In 1937, the Hindenburg made a flight across the Atlantic to the USA.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Thousands of people came to watch its landing.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>The beautiful, gleaming, airship came gently down to its landing point.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>Suddenly, it gave a jerk.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>There was a flash of flame and it exploded.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>A moment later its whole length crumpled to the ground.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
		  </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Its crew and passengers all died.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
   </paragraph>
</APageParagraph>
